.TH INCUSBOX-ENTER 1 "2026" "incusbox 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
incusbox-enter \- enter an incusbox container
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B incusbox enter
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.I NAME
.RI [ COMMAND
.RI [ ARGS... ]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Starts the named container if it is not already running, waits for
.BR incusbox-init (1)
to complete, then opens an interactive shell (or runs
.IR COMMAND )
inside the container as the host user.
.PP
The wait mechanism checks for
.I /run/incusbox-ready
(written by
.BR incusbox-init (1)
on completion). For containers using the exec-injection path (no cloud-init),
this file is written synchronously before
.B incusbox enter
is called, so the wait returns immediately.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-s " SHELL" "\fR,\fP \-\-shell " SHELL
Shell to use inside the container. Defaults to the user's login shell.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-tty
Disable TTY allocation (useful for scripting).
.TP
.B \-r ", " \-\-root
Use rootful
.BR incus (1).
.TP
.B \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Show verbose output.
.TP
.B \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Exits with the exit status of the command run inside the container.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR incusbox (1),
.BR incusbox-create (1),
.BR incusbox-init (1),
.BR incus-exec (1)
